  "prompt": "What countries have extradition treaties with UAE?",
  "response": "The United Arab Emirates (UAE) has extradition treaties with numerous countries. These treaties facilitate the process of extradition, where one country can request the handover of a person accused or convicted of a crime from another country. The list of countries with which the UAE has extradition treaties includes, but is not limited to:\n\n1. India\n2. Pakistan\n3. United Kingdom\n4. United States\n5. France\n6. Australia\n7. Canada\n8. China\n9. Egypt\n10. Saudi Arabia\n\nAdditionally, the UAE has extradition agreements with several other countries across Europe, Asia, Africa, and the Americas. The specifics of each treaty, including the types of crimes covered and the legal procedures involved, can vary. Therefore, it is advisable to consult legal experts or official government sources for detailed information regarding extradition arrangements between the UAE and specific countries.",
